weary /ˈwɪərɪ/

(wearier,weariest) 

1. ADJ If you are weary , you are very tired. 疲惫的 

例： Rachel looked pale and weary. 雷切尔看起来苍白而疲惫。 

2. ADJ If you are weary of something, you have become tired of it and have lost your enthusiasm for it. 对…感到厌倦 [v-link ADJ 'of' n/-ing] 

例： They're getting awfully weary of this silly war. 他们对这场愚蠢的战争感到极其厌倦。

